## Mapping of each change to Dan's comment (all on PR #7306)
- googleAdk.ts:1310 "We've hoisted all of the other state that's aware of this
  CJS/ESM dual-hazard thing into state.ts. Thoughts on doing that here?"
  -> Moved the plugin holder from globalSingleton('_weave_adk_instrumentation')
     to state.integrations.googleAdk.plugin. THIS is why state.ts changed:
     added googleAdk.plugin slot to the State type + defaultState(). The two
     files are one coupled change.
- googleAdk.ts:1419 "Thoughts on us starting to try to type these? import type
  * as GoogleADK ... commonPatchGoogleADK(exports: typeof GoogleADK)"
  -> Added `import type * as GoogleADK from '@google/adk'`; typed
     commonPatchGoogleADK(exports: typeof GoogleADK) and
     patchRunnerClass(RunnerClass: typeof GoogleADK.Runner). patchRunnerClass
     still views proto as an indexable bag (prototype swap is inherently
     dynamic) via a localized cast.
- googleAdk.ts:141 "Are we able to pick the fields from PluginManager ...
  Pick<PluginManager,...>" + :146 "use the Runner type directly, or pick from
  it?"  -> Deleted both hand-rolled interfaces (AdkPluginManager, AdkRunnerLike
     shape) and set `type AdkRunnerLike = Pick<GoogleADK.Runner,'pluginManager'>`
     which pulls the real PluginManager type transitively.
- googleAdk.ts:149 "Looks like this isn't used externally." -> Unexported
  WEAVE_ADK_PLUGIN_NAME. Verified: grep across src+test finds zero external
  importers.
- googleAdk.ts:1324 + :1358 "Do we need to guard against null?" -> Removed the
  runtime `!pluginManager || typeof getPlugin !== 'function'` guards and the
  `runner?.pluginManager?.` optional chaining; lean on the Runner type and the
  existing try/catch boundary (instrumentation must never break a user run).
  Documented that reasoning in the ensurePluginRegistered docstring.
- googleAdk.ts:1360 "What were we trying to do via instanceof? ... could throw
  this sort of property checking into an isWeavePlugin guard." -> Added
  isWeavePlugin(plugin): plugin is WeaveAdkPlugin, duck-typing
  finishInterruptedInvocation; used in finishInterruptedInvocations.

